entry.title: Uruguay Reflects Latin American Drift From U.S., Turn to China
entry.content: Having tried and failed to get a free-trade deal with the U.S., Uruguay is now negotiating one with Beijing amid a Chinese charm offensive, reflecting similar situations across the region.

entry.title: Same Drug, Two Prices: Why The Higher Price Prevails
entry.content: Patients are paying hundreds of dollars more for a prescription than they would have to if their health plan chose to cover a lower-priced twin.
